940 and settled in New York. This long-delayed appreciation of the Jewish architect reveals the extraordinary importance of his early work in Germany and his contributions to modern synagogue architecture in the US.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aArchitectszGermanyy20th centuryvBiography. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh1 aBehrmann, Roland08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97830382160010 cprintz978303821468740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303821087040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783038210870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783038210870.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKAb2015